text: The Austrian Regional League Central () is a third-tier division of Austrian football re-introduced in the 1994–95 season. It covers the Austrian states of Carinthia (with East Tyrol), Styria and Upper Austria and is one of three leagues at this level. == Recent league champions == The most recent league champions: {| class="wikitable" |- align="center" style="background:#dfdfdf" !width="80"| Season !width="200"| Club |- |2012–13 |LASK Linz |- |2013–14 |LASK Linz |- |2014–15 |SK Austria Klagenfurt |- |2015–16 |FC Blau-Weiß Linz |- |2016–17 |TSV Hartberg |- |2017–18 |SV Lafnitz |- |2018–19 |Grazer AK |} ==References== ==External links== *Regional League Central (in German only) *Austrian Regional League Central tables & results at soccerway.com Cen
